                            <comment id="17048635" author="jbonofre" created="Sun, 1 Mar 2020 17:06:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-7433&quot; title=&quot;Use short rendering of exception/throwable in log by default&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-7433&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-7433&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17050434" author="jbonofre" created="Tue, 3 Mar 2020 17:51:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Generally speaking, if there&apos;s an exception, it makes sense to display the stack trace (it&apos;s the only way to investigate an issue).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if your issue is related to logstash/filebeat, I now changed to use &lt;tt&gt;EnhancedPatternLayout&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;conf/log4j.properties&lt;/tt&gt;. Thanks to that, you can now use &lt;tt&gt;ConversionPattern&lt;/tt&gt; like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
log4j.appender.logfile.layour.ConversionPattern=%d | %-5p | %m | %c | %t%n%replace(%throwable){\n}{ } &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
